This paper is about personalized web search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed algorithm involves machine learning techniques such as multi-armed bandit (cs.LG) and can generalize well to new users and URLs (cs.AI). The focus on improving user experience suggests a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques to extract features from search queries and web pages could also place this paper in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
